\subsection{Oppgave 4.6.2}
Vi skal finne verdier $x_1,x_2,x_3$ slik at 
\[
  x_1 \left( \begin{array}{r} 1 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{array} \right) +
  x_2 \left( \begin{array}{r} 1 \\ 2 \\ 1  \end{array} \right) +
  x_3 \left( \begin{array}{r} 3 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{array} \right)
  =
  \left( \begin{array}{r} -2 \\ 5 \\ 1 \end{array} \right).
\]
Vi danner oss den utvidede matrisen til likningssystemet og radreduserer:
\begin{eqnarray*}
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 3 & -2 \\
0  & 2 &-1 &  5 \\ 
-1 & 1 & 2 &  1 
\end{array}
\right)
&\stackrel{III+I}{\sim}&
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 3 & -2 \\
0  & 2 &-1 &  5 \\ 
0  & 2 & 5 & -1 
\end{array}
\right)
\stackrel{III-II}{\sim}
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 3 & -2 \\
0  & 2 &-1 &  5 \\ 
0  & 0 & 6 & -6 
\end{array}
\right) \\
&\stackrel{\frac{1}{6}III}{\sim}&
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 3 & -2 \\
0  & 2 &-1 &  5 \\ 
0  & 0 & 1 & -1 
\end{array}
\right)
\stackrel{II+III,I-3III}{\sim}
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 0 &  1 \\
0  & 2 & 0 &  4 \\ 
0  & 0 & 1 & -1 
\end{array}
\right) \\
&\stackrel{\frac{1}{2}II}{\sim}&
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 1 & 0 &  1 \\
0  & 1 & 0 &  2 \\ 
0  & 0 & 1 & -1 
\end{array}
\right)
\stackrel{I-II}{\sim}
\left(
\begin{array}{rrrr}
1  & 0 & 0 & -1 \\
0  & 1 & 0 &  2 \\ 
0  & 0 & 1 & -1 
\end{array}
\right).
\end{eqnarray*}
Vi ser at $x_1=-1,x_2=2,x_3=-1$, slik at 
\[
  (-1) \left( \begin{array}{r} 1 \\ 0 \\ -1 \end{array} \right) +
  2    \left( \begin{array}{r} 1 \\ 2 \\ 1  \end{array} \right) 
  (-1) \left( \begin{array}{r} 3 \\ -1 \\ 2 \end{array} \right)
  =
  \left( \begin{array}{r} -2 \\ 5 \\ 1 \end{array} \right).
\]